AUXILIARY_DESCRIPTIONS.tractor-trailer: Vehicle used to transport undocumented aliens, also used for transporting commercial equipment and stopped at Freer, Texas on June 12, 2014; involved in an incident where contraband was detected by a dog and found to have ten undocumented aliens hidden in its closets and beds. On July 8, 2014, it was used by Raymond McMillon to transport Ramon De La Cruz and Jorge Miguel Hernandez-Gomez, who were discovered hidden in the tractor's sleeper area. Used in offenses for which Raymond McMillon was convicted and sentenced to 41 months' imprisonment. Involved in a search at Freer, Texas, where the consent of Zeba Williams was questioned. Searched with Raymond McMillon as a passenger claiming a possessory interest due to an agreement to help drive it for commercial purposes. Featured in a checkpoint video that showed unclear footage of its interior. Subject of a court case regarding a motion to suppress evidence from a checkpoint stop and search. Involved in a hearing on motions to suppress and for discovery of canine records. Used to transport aliens from an empty parking lot through Freer, Texas. Also involved in a conspiracy where aliens paid thousands of dollars to be smuggled into the United States.
